---
/**
 * Privacy Policy — required by GDPR Art. 13 (transparency at point of data collection).
 * Linked from every page footer and from the account sign-up form.
 *
 * Versions are tracked so that future updates can be distinguished from what a
 * specific user consented to at sign-up time (privacy_policy_version stored in
 * account_profiles).
 */
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

export const PRIVACY_POLICY_VERSION = 'v1-2026-04';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Matlu Codex collects, uses, and protects your personal data."
>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="meta">Version {PRIVACY_POLICY_VERSION} &mdash; April 2026</p>

  <p class="lead">
    This policy explains what personal data Matlu Codex collects, why we collect it,
    who sees it, and what rights you have. We have written it in plain language because
    many of our users are children, and their parents and guardians deserve a clear
    explanation — not a wall of legal text.
  </p>

  <section>
    <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      Matlu Codex is the community hub for the <em>Core Warden</em> game, part of the
      Matlu multiworld project run by Fills Pills (Filip Marzuki). For GDPR purposes,
      Fills Pills is the <strong>data controller</strong>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Contact: <a href="https://github.com/FilipMarzuki/matlu/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        open a GitHub issue
      </a> or email us at the address listed on the GitHub profile. We aim to respond within
      30 days as required by Art. 12(3).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. What we collect and why</h2>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Data</th>
          <th>Why we collect it</th>
          <th>Lawful basis (GDPR Art. 6)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Parent / guardian email</strong></td>
          <td>To send magic sign-in links and important account notices.</td>
          <td>Consent (Art. 6(1)(a)) + contract performance (Art. 6(1)(b))</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Account handle</strong></td>
          <td>To display on your public creator profile page.</td>
          <td>Consent (Art. 6(1)(a))</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Child&rsquo;s first name / nickname and optional age</strong></td>
          <td>To credit the creator of each submitted creature. No surnames, photos, school, or location are collected.</td>
          <td>Parental consent (Art. 8 + Art. 6(1)(a))</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Creature submissions</strong> (drawings, descriptions, answers)</td>
          <td>To display on the wiki and optionally include in the game per the <a href="/creatures/license">Creature License</a>.</td>
          <td>Consent (Art. 6(1)(a))</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Creature drafts</strong></td>
          <td>To let you resume work-in-progress submissions across devices.</td>
          <td>Consent (Art. 6(1)(a))</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>GDPR action log</strong></td>
          <td>To maintain an audit trail when you exercise data-subject rights (export, delete, pause).</td>
          <td>Legal obligation (Art. 6(1)(c), Art. 5(2))</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p class="note">
      We do <strong>not</strong> collect IP addresses beyond Supabase infrastructure defaults,
      use tracking cookies, run analytics, or share data with advertising networks.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Who else sees your data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Supabase</strong> (EU region) — our database and authentication provider.
        Data is stored in an EU data centre. Supabase Inc. (US parent) processes data under
        Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) to cover any unavoidable cross-border flows
        (Art. 46 transfer mechanism).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Vercel</strong> — serves the Matlu Codex website. Vercel processes request
        metadata (IP, user agent) to route traffic; this is covered by Vercel&rsquo;s DPA.
      </li>
      <li>
        We do <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or share personal data with any third party
        for marketing or analytics purposes.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>4. How long we keep it</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Data</th><th>Retention period</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Active account data (profile, kids, drafts)</td><td>As long as the account is active.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Unsubmitted drafts</td><td>90 days after last update, then auto-deleted.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Rejected creature submissions</td><td>30 days after rejection, then auto-deleted (row + artwork file).</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Approved creature submissions</td><td>Kept indefinitely unless you request deletion or anonymisation.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Inactive accounts</td><td>We email a warning after 24 months of inactivity. If there is no response within 30 days, the account and all associated data are deleted.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>GDPR action log entries</td><td>Kept for 3 years for compliance audit purposes.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>5. Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Under GDPR you have the following rights. You can exercise most of them from
      <a href="/account/settings">Account Settings</a>.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Access (Art. 15)</strong> — download a JSON file of everything we hold about you via <a href="/account/export">Account &rsaquo; Export my data</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Rectification (Art. 16)</strong> — update your handle or your children&rsquo;s names in Account Settings. For approved submissions, use the &ldquo;Request edit&rdquo; button (emails the admin).</li>
      <li><strong>Erasure / right to be forgotten (Art. 17)</strong> — delete your account from <a href="/account/delete">Account &rsaquo; Delete account</a>. Choose <em>full delete</em> (removes everything) or <em>anonymise</em> (approved creatures stay on the wiki but are unattributed).</li>
      <li><strong>Data portability (Art. 20)</strong> — the same JSON export from the access request is machine-readable and structured.</li>
      <li><strong>Restrict processing (Art. 18)</strong> — pause your account in Account Settings. Your data is retained but no new processing happens.</li>
      <li><strong>Object (Art. 21)</strong> — contact us to object to a specific processing activity.</li>
      <li><strong>Withdraw consent (Art. 7(3))</strong> — withdrawing consent triggers the erasure flow described above.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      All data-subject actions are logged in our GDPR audit trail. We will respond within
      one month (Art. 12(3)).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>6. Children</h2>
    <p>
      This service is <strong>not for children to use directly</strong>. Only parents or
      guardians aged 18 or older may create accounts (EU Art. 8 — age of digital consent).
      Children submit creatures via a grown-up&rsquo;s account. We do not knowingly collect
      personal data directly from children.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you believe a child has created an account directly, please contact us immediately
      so we can delete it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>7. Cookies and tracking</h2>
    <p>
      We use <strong>one session cookie</strong> set by Supabase Auth to keep you signed in.
      No tracking cookies, advertising cookies, or fingerprinting are used. You can sign out
      at any time to clear the session cookie.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>8. Security</h2>
    <p>
      All data is encrypted at rest (Supabase Postgres, AES-256) and in transit (HTTPS,
      enforced by Vercel). We use passwordless magic-link authentication — there are no
      passwords to steal. Row-Level Security (RLS) policies in the database ensure users
      can only access their own data. No service-role key is present in client-side code.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      If we make material changes, we will email you and ask you to accept the new version
      on your next sign-in. The version identifier at the top of this page and stored in
      your account record tells you exactly which version you agreed to.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>10. Complaints</h2>
    <p>
      If you are unhappy with how we handle your data, you have the right to lodge a complaint
      with your local data protection authority:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Sweden: <a href="https://www.imy.se" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Integritetsskyddsmyndigheten (IMY)</a></li>
      <li>UK: <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Information Commissioner&rsquo;s Office (ICO)</a></li>
      <li>EU: find your national DPA at <a href="https://edpb.europa.eu/about-edpb/about-edpb/members_en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">edpb.europa.eu</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .meta {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--accent-hi);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  th {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.8rem;
    background: var(--surface-hi);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  td {
    padding: 0.6rem 0.8rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    vertical-align: top;
    line-height: 1.5;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
  }

  ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  li {
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .note {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    background: var(--surface-hi);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
</style>
